'''Udochukwu Nwoko''' (born [[15 October]] [[1984]] in [[Abia State|Abia]], [[Nigeria]]) is a [[Malta|Maltese]] professional [[football (soccer)|football]]er currently playing for [[Leix<U+00F5>es S.C.|Leix<U+00F5>es]] in [[Portugal]].  A small but agile attacker, he can also play just behind the strikers.  He is not an out and out goal scorer, but prefers holding up play and providing the final pass to attackers.

==Football career==
Nwoko started his career at Maltese club [[Hibernians F.C.|Hibernians]] at the age 14, having moved to Malta with the hope that it would lead him to one of the top leagues in Europe.{{fact|date=December 2007}}  He then moved onto Maltese clubs [[Mosta F.C.|Mosta]] and [[Marsaxlokk F.C.|Marsaxlokk]], where he was part of the 2006&ndash;07 championship-winning squad.

In 2007, he moved to Portuguese club [[Leix<U+00F5>es S.C.|Leix<U+00F5>es]], but has been linked with a move to [[Premier League]] club [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] in the January 2008 transfer window.<ref>{{cite news | date=[[2007-12-28]] | url=http://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/2007/12/28/royals-net-nwoko-89520-20267252/ | title=Royals net Nwoko | work=[[Daily Mirror]] | accessdate=2007-12-28}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Nwoko is married to a Maltese woman, and obtained Maltese citizenship in August 2007{{fact|date=December 2007}} and therefore became eligible to play for the [[Malta national football team]].  He began playing for Malta on [[13 October]] [[2007]] when he made his debut against [[Hungary national football team|Hungary]]. 

